FRENCH.SOT: Celui Qui S'endore dans la Glace

ENGLISH.SOT:
You can find 'em near a giant crevasse low on
the eastern side of the Valuan continent.
FRENCH.SOT:
Vous les trouverez près d'une crevasse géante au
bas de la côte est du continent Valuan.
GERMAN.SOT:
You can find 'em near a giant crevasse low on
the eastern side of the Valuan continent.
SPANISH.SOT:
You can find 'em near a giant crevasse low on
the eastern side of the Valuan continent.

ENGLISH.SOT:
You might try lookin' near the big crevasse
low on the Eastern side of Valua…
FRENCH.SOT:
Vous devriez chercher près de la grande crevasse
au bas de la côte est du continent Valuan……
GERMAN.SOT:
You might try lookin' near the big crevasse
low on the Eastern side of Valua…
SPANISH.SOT:
You might try lookin' near the big crevasse
low on the Eastern side of Valua

ENGLISH.SOT:
A natural phenomenon that
can be seen underneath
the Valuan continent,
it is said to be caused by
electricity from the
Yellow Moon Stones in the
Valuan soil. Some say that
it is caused by a giant
creature that lies deep
inside the ground.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un phénomène naturel
visible sous le continent
Valuan, on dit que c'est
dû à l'électricité des
pierres de lune jaunes
dans le sol Valuan.
Certains racontent que
c'est dû à une créature
géante allongée dans les
profondeurs du sol.
GERMAN.SOT:
A natural phenomenon that
can be seen underneath
the Valuan continent,
it is said to be caused by
electricity from the
Yellow Moon Stones in the
Valuan soil. Some say that
it is caused by a giant
creature that lies deep
inside the ground.

ENGLISH.SOT:
They've been seen flying in the skies north of a
mountain called Kazai, in Yafutoma.
FRENCH.SOT:
Ils ont été aperçus volant dans les cieux au
nord d'une montagne appellée Kazai, à Yafutoma.
GERMAN.SOT:
They've been seen flying in the skies north of a
mountain called Kazai, in Yafutoma.
SPANISH.SOT:
They've been seen flying in the skies north of a
mountain called Kazai, in Yafutoma.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Some guys who went to Yafutoma with the Armada
say they saw 'em north of a big mountian.
FRENCH.SOT:
Des hommes partis à Yafutoma avec l'Armada les
ont vus au nord d'une grande montagne.
GERMAN.SOT:
Some guys who went to Yafutoma with the Armada
say they saw 'em north of a big mountian.
SPANISH.SOT:
Some guys who went to Yafutoma with the Armada
say they saw 'em north of a big mountian.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The Wanderbirds are large
migratory birds from the
far North, revered since
ancient times as symbols
of long life. Its cry is
rarely ever heard, but the
clarity and beauty of
their song is said to put
all other birds to shame.
FRENCH.SOT:
Les oiseaux errants sont
de grands oiseaux
migrateurs venus du grand
nord, vénérés depuis les
temps anciens comme
symbole de longévité. Il
est rare   d'entendre leur
cri, mais la clarté et la
beauté de leur chant
embarrasse tous les autres oiseaux.
GERMAN.SOT:
The Wanderbirds are large
migratory birds from the
far North, revered since
ancient times as symbols
of long life. Its cry is
rarely ever heard, but the
clarity and beauty of
their song is said to put
all other birds to shame.

The Wanderbirds are large

their song is said to put
all other birds to shame.

ENGLISH.SOT:
They live on the bottom of the Valuan continent,
on the eastern side.
FRENCH.SOT:
Ils vivent au fin fond du continent Valuan, sur
la côte est.
GERMAN.SOT:
They live on the bottom of the Valuan continent,
on the eastern side.
SPANISH.SOT:
They live on the bottom of the Valuan continent,
on the eastern side.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I hear they live in low altitudes… you might try
looking on the bottom of the Valuan continent.
FRENCH.SOT:
Ils vivent à basse altitude…... Vous devriez
chercher au fin fond du continent Valuan.
GERMAN.SOT:
I hear they live in low altitudes… you might try
looking on the bottom of the Valuan continent.
SPANISH.SOT:
I hear they live in low altitudes?you might try
looking on the bottom of the Valuan continent.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A strange creature that
spends its entire life
hanging upside down by
digging its claws into the
rock face. Until it was
discovered underneath the
Valuan continent, it was
thought to be a myth. Its
intelligence and ferocity
belie its cute appearance.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une étrange créature qui
passe sa vie suspendue à
l'envers en enfonçant ses
griffes dans la paroi du
rocher. Les gens croyaient
que c'était un mythe
jusqu'à ce qu'elle soit
découverte sous le
continent Valuan. Son air
mignon cache bien son intelligence et sa férocité.
GERMAN.SOT:
A strange creature that

hanging upside down by
digging its claws into the
rock face. Until it was
discovered underneath the
Valuan continent, it was

intelligence and ferocity
belie its cute appearance.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The ruins are on on the continent of Ixa'taka,
on a plateau that rises above the clouds.
FRENCH.SOT:
Les ruines sont sur le continent d'Ixa'taka, sur
un plateau qui s'élève au dessus des nuages.
GERMAN.SOT:
The ruins are on on the continent of Ixa'taka,
on a plateau that rises above the clouds.
SPANISH.SOT:
The ruins are on on the continent of Ixa'taka,
on a plateau that rises above the clouds.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Apparently it's somewhere on the continent of
Ixa'taka… maybe somewhere up high?
FRENCH.SOT:
Apparemment, il est quelque part sur le
continent Ixa'taka… Peut-être à haute altitude ?
GERMAN.SOT:
Apparently it's somewhere on the continent of
Ixa'taka… maybe somewhere up high?
SPANISH.SOT:
Apparently it's somewhere on the continent of
Ixa'taka?maybe somewhere up high?

ENGLISH.SOT:
A civilization once
flourished in this land,
under the Green Moon. The
observatory built on the
Ixa'takan plateau speaks
to their advanced study of
astronomy--but, they could
do naught but watch, as
a shower of Moon Stones
destroyed their culture.
FRENCH.SOT:
Jadis une civilisation a
prospéré sur cette terre,
sous la Lune Verte.
L'observatoire construit
sur le plateau Ixa'takan
témoigne de leur
connaissance en astronomie
mais ils regardèrent
impuissants la pluie de
Pierres de Lune détruire leur civilisation.
GERMAN.SOT:
A civilization once
flourished in this land,
under the Green Moon. The
observatory built on the
Ixa'takan plateau speaks
to their advanced study of
astronomy--but, they could
do naught but watch, as
a shower of Moon Stones
destroyed their culture.

ENGLISH.SOT:
There's an island with a waterfall that feeds
a lake in Ixa'taka. Look in the forest there.
FRENCH.SOT:
Il y a une île avec une cascade qui alimente un
lac à Ixa'taka. Cherchez dans la forêt alentour.
GERMAN.SOT:
There's an island with a waterfall that feeds
a lake in Ixa'taka. Look in the forest there.
SPANISH.SOT:
There's an island with a waterfall that feeds
a lake in Ixa'taka. Look in the forest there.

ENGLISH.SOT:
They live somewhere in Ixa'taka, on some island
with a forest and a waterfall…
FRENCH.SOT:
Ils vivent quelque part à Ixa'taka, sur une île
avec une forêt et une cascade…
GERMAN.SOT:
They live somewhere in Ixa'taka, on some island
with a forest and a waterfall…
SPANISH.SOT:
They live somewhere in Ixa'taka, on some island
with a forest and a waterfall

ENGLISH.SOT:
An ancient species that
predates the Ixa'takan
civilization, the
Alupas live quietly in
the forest. Their calm,
proud demeanor has earned
them the name “Sages of
the Forest.” They are also
known for choosing their
mates for life.
FRENCH.SOT:
Espèce ancienne qui
existait avant la
civilisation Ixa'takan,
les Alupas vivent
paisiblement dans la
forêt. Leur comportement
fier et calme leur ont
valu le nom de “Sages de
la Forêt”. Ils choisissent
leurs partenaires pour la vie.
GERMAN.SOT:
An ancient species that

civilization, the
Alupas live quietly in

them the name “Sages of
the Forest.” They are also
known for choosing their
mates for life.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I hear that Ixa'takans usually settle on islands
where these fruits grow.
FRENCH.SOT:
J'ai entendu dire que les Ixa'takans peuplent
généralement des îles où ces fruits poussent.
GERMAN.SOT:
I hear that Ixa'takans usually settle on islands
where these fruits grow.
SPANISH.SOT:
I hear that Ixa'takans usually settle on islands
where these fruits grow.

ENGLISH.SOT:
It's some kinda food, right? It's probably near
a settlement, then, don't you think?
FRENCH.SOT:
Ça se mange, non ? Ils ne sont sûrement pas loin
d'une colonie, vous ne croyez pas?
GERMAN.SOT:
It's some kinda food, right? It's probably near
a settlement, then, don't you think?
SPANISH.SOT:
It's some kinda food, right? It's probably near
a settlement, then, don't you think?

ENGLISH.SOT:
A vined plant that hangs
from the bottom of the
continent. Its stem
contains a powerful
hallucinogen, and it has
been used for medicinal
and religious purposes
through the ages. It is
also commonly used in
local delicacies.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une plante grimpante
suspendue au bout du
continent. Sa tige
contient un hallucinogène
puissant, utilisé à
travers les siècles à des
fins médicales et
religieuses. C'est aussi
un mets délicat de la
région.
GERMAN.SOT:

continent. Its stem
contains a powerful
hallucinogen, and it has
been used for medicinal
and religious purposes
through the ages. It is
also commonly used in
local delicacies.

ENGLISH.SOT:
It's on the plains near the large lake in
Ixa'taka, with a waterfall feeding into it.
FRENCH.SOT:
Il est sur les plaines d'Ixa'taka près du grand
lac alimenté par une cascade.
GERMAN.SOT:
It's on the plains near the large lake in
Ixa'taka, with a waterfall feeding into it.
SPANISH.SOT:
It's on the plains near the large lake in
Ixa'taka, with a waterfall feeding into it.

ENGLISH.SOT:
There's a big lake in Ixa'taka. I hear there's
something near there.
FRENCH.SOT:
A Ixa'taka se trouve un lac géant. Il paraît
qu'il y a quelque chose d'intéressant là-bas.
GERMAN.SOT:
There's a big lake in Ixa'taka. I hear there's
something near there.
SPANISH.SOT:
There's a big lake in Ixa'taka. I hear there's
something near there.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The wings and tail of the
Great Bird are said to
indicate the equinoxes of
the ancient Ixa'takan
verdilunar calendar.
Figures of other animals
once dotted the plain, but
they have been swallowed
by the expanding forest,
leaving only the Bird.
FRENCH.SOT:
Les ailes et les plumes de
la queue du Grand Oiseau
sont supposées indiquer
les équinoxes de l'ancien
calendrier verdilunaire
Ixa'takan. Jadis, d'autres
formes d'animaux
jonchaient la plaine, mais
elles ont été englouties
par l'avancée de la forêt, n'épargnant que l'Oiseau.
GERMAN.SOT:
The wings and tail of the
Great Bird are said to
indicate the equinoxes of
the ancient Ixa'takan
verdilunar calendar.
Figures of other animals
once dotted the plain, but
they have been swallowed
by the expanding forest,
leaving only the Bird.

ENGLISH.SOT:
It's on an island near the middle of North
Ocean. Once you get there, you'll see it.
FRENCH.SOT:
Il est sur une île près du centre de l'Océan
Nord. Vous le verrez en arrivant.
GERMAN.SOT:
It's on an island near the middle of North
Ocean. Once you get there, you'll see it.
SPANISH.SOT:
It's on an island near the middle of North
Ocean. Once you get there, you'll see it.

ENGLISH.SOT:
It's somewhere in North Ocean. Of course, North
Ocean is a pretty big place…
FRENCH.SOT:
Il est quelque part dans l'Océan Nord.
Évidemment, l'Océan Nord est plutôt grand…
GERMAN.SOT:
It's somewhere in North Ocean. Of course, North
Ocean is a pretty big place…
SPANISH.SOT:
It's somewhere in North Ocean. Of course, North
Ocean is a pretty big place

ENGLISH.SOT:
An enormous rock formation
that looks like a rocking
chair. The claw marks on
its surface have given
rise to many stories--some
speak of a giant green
creature that once perched
here, or of a hairy beast
that was lulled to sleep
by the rocking motion.
FRENCH.SOT:
La formation d'un rocher
énorme qui ressemble à un
rocking chair. Les marques
de griffe à la surface ont
suscité bien des
histoires: certains
parlent d'une créature
géante verte qui jadis se
perchait ici, d'autres
d'une bête velue qui s'endormait en se balançant.
GERMAN.SOT:

that looks like a rocking
chair. The claw marks on
its surface have given

creature that once perched
here, or of a hairy beast
that was lulled to sleep
by the rocking motion.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,
between Valua and Ixa'taka.
FRENCH.SOT:
Essayez de chercher au beau milieu de l'Océan
Nord, entre Valua et Ixa'taka.
GERMAN.SOT:
Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,
between Valua and Ixa'taka.
SPANISH.SOT:
Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,
between Valua and Ixa'taka.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I heard rumors about these from some Valuans on
their way back from the new continent.
FRENCH.SOT:
Des Valuans sur le chemin du retour du nouveau
continent m'en ont parlé.
GERMAN.SOT:
I heard rumors about these from some Valuans on
their way back from the new continent.
SPANISH.SOT:
I heard rumors about these from some Valuans on
their way back from the new continent.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Huge geometric shapes that
mysteriously appear on the
ground overnight. Reports
have been very frequent
lately. Old records speak
of a similar phenomenon,
and mention 2 or 3 glowing
balls of light that appear
the night before the
shapes are found.
FRENCH.SOT:
D'immenses formes
géométriques qui
apparaissent
mystérieusement la nuit
sur le sol. Depuis peu,
elles ont souvent été
vues. De vieux récits
parlent d'un phénomène
similaire mentionnant 2 ou
3 boules lumineuses qui apparaissent la nuit précédant l'apparition de la forme.
GERMAN.SOT:

shapes are found.

Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,

FRENCH.SOT:
Essayez de chercher au beau milieu de l'Océan
Nord, entre Valua et Montezuma.
GERMAN.SOT:
Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,
Valua and Ixa'taka.
SPANISH.SOT:
Try looking right in the middle of North Ocean,
Valua and Ixa'taka.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I heard about this from some Valuans who came
back from the new continent. Fairies, eh?
FRENCH.SOT:
Des Valuans sur le chemin du retour du nouveau
continent m'en ont parlé. Des fées, hein ?
GERMAN.SOT:
I heard about this from some Valuans who came
back from the new continent. Fairies, eh?
SPANISH.SOT:
I heard about this from some Valuans who came
back from the new continent. Fairies, eh?

ENGLISH.SOT:
“I woke up in the middle
of the night, and saw
something glowing out near
some unpopulated islands.
I thought I was just
seeing things at first,
but then the lights
started moving around in
these weird patterns…”
- An anonymous sailor
FRENCH.SOT:
“Je me suis réveillé au
milieu de la nuit, et j'ai
vu quelque chose briller
dehors près des îles non-
habitées. Au début j'ai
cru que j'imaginais des
choses, mais les formes
ont commencé à bouger et à
former ces étranges
dessins…” - Un marin anonyme
GERMAN.SOT:
“I woke up in the middle
of the night, and saw

ENGLISH.SOT:
Look for an island to the north of the Moon
Stone Mountain in Ixa'taka.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cherchez une île au nord du Mont Pierre de Lune
à Ixa'taka.
GERMAN.SOT:
Look for an island to the north of the Moon
Stone Mountain in Ixa'taka.
SPANISH.SOT:
Look for an island to the north of the Moon
Stone Mountain in Ixa'taka.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I heard that it's somewhere on the new

ENGLISH.SOT:
A tribe of women that
lives on a small island in
Ixa'taka. They are skilled
and fearsome warriors.
They raid nearby villages
twice a year to kidnap
men. The numbers of men
in nearby tribes have
been almost reduced to
nothing.

Une tribu de femmes qui
occupe une petite île à
Ixa'taka. Ce sont de
redoutables guerrières.
Elles attaquent les
villages environnants 2
fois par an pour kidnapper
les hommes. Il ne reste
quasiment plus d'hommes
dans les tribus voisines.

A huge stone face that
stands quietly, buried
deep in the forests of
Ixa'taka. The stones
have been fitted so
tightly together that
not even an insect could
crawl between them. It
is a remnant of an
ancient civilization.

Une énorme paroi en
pierre, ensevelie au fin
fond des forêts
d'Ixa'taka. Les pierres
sont tellement rapprochées
qu'un insecte ne pourrait
même pas se glisser entre.
C'est le vestige d'une
civilisation ancienne.

This stone palace was once
the site of ceremonies
based on the ancient lunar
calendar, built during the
reign of the Moon Kings.
This place flourished as
the center of Ixa'takan
civilization for ages, but
was destroyed several
years ago by the Valuans.

Autrefois ce palais de
pierre fût un lieu de
cérémonies basées sur
l'ancien calendrier

le règne des Rois Lune.
Cet endroit prospéra et
devint le centre de la civilisation Ixa'takan
pendant très longtemps, mais il a été détruit il y
a plusieurs années par les Valuans.

Most people on this world
do not even know that a
continent exists across
South Ocean. The discovery
of this lush, rich
continent with a long
history has demonstrated
the possibility that even
more unknown, undiscovered
lands may await.

La plupart des gens
ignorent l'existence d'un
continent au-delà de
l'Océan Sud. La découverte
de ces Terres luxuriantes
au passé riche démontre
qu'il reste peut-être
encore d'autres terres
inconnues à découvrir.

A strange bird that lives
on islands of ice. Its
small wings are not suited
for flight, so it feeds by
jumping for fish that
float nearby. They are
model parents--males and
females take turns caring
for an egg, never leaving
it until it hatches.

Un étrange oiseau qui vit
sur des îles de glace. Ses
petites ailes ne sont pas
adaptées au vol, alors

sont des parents modèles :
males et femelles veillent
sur l'oeuf à tour de rôle,
ne le laissant jamais seul jusqu'à éclosion.

Valuan ships returning

from his voyage around the
world, it became known
that the world was round.

that we would find a girl

stern with her at first,
but it looks like she's
staying with us tonight.

ENGLISH.SOT:
I… I'm speechless. For
probably the first time
in my life, I don't know
what to say. I never even
dreamed that this many
Air Pirates would come
together to fight. Aika,
Fina, Gilder, Drachma,
Enrique… thank you all…
Tomorrow, we make history.

journal entry. The future

ENGLISH.SOT:
Summons all active members of the Delphinus
crew. Attack varies depending on crew.    SP ALL
FRENCH.SOT:
Appel les membres actifs de l'équipage du
Delphinus. Attaque varie selon équipage. ES TOUS
GERMAN.SOT:
Summons all active members of the Delphinus
crew. Attack varies depending on crew.    SP ALL
SPANISH.SOT:
Convoca a los miembros de la tripulación del
Delphinus. El ataque depende de ellos.   SEP ALL

ENGLISH.SOT:
Combines the power of all 4 party members to
call upon an ancient power.               SP ALL
FRENCH.SOT:
Concentre le pouvoir des 4 membres du groupe
pour invoquer un pouvoir ancien.         ES TOUS
GERMAN.SOT:
Combines the power of all 4 party members to
call upon an ancient power.               SP ALL
SPANISH.SOT:
Combina el poder de los 4 miembros del grupo
para convocar un poder ancestral.        SEP ALL

ENGLISH.SOT:
Vyse received these swords as a gift from his
father, Dyne. It is light, with a short blade.
FRENCH.SOT:
Vyse a reçu ces épées en cadeau de son père,
Dyne. Elles sont légères avec des lames courtes.
GERMAN.SOT:
Vyse received these swords as a gift from his
father, Dyne. It is light, with a short blade.
SPANISH.SOT:
Vyse recibió estos sables como regalo de su
padre, Dyne. La hoja es corta y ligera.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The favorite sword among Air Pirates in the Mid
Ocean area. It is light and very easy to wield.
FRENCH.SOT:
Épée préférée des Pirates de
l'Océan Central. Légère et très facile à manier.
GERMAN.SOT:
The favorite sword among Air Pirates in the Mid
Ocean area. It is light and very easy to wield.
SPANISH.SOT:
El sable preferido por los piratas aéreos del
Océano Medio. Ligero y fácil de manejar.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A cutlass used by Pirates and fishermen alike.
Its edge is perfect for cleaning fish.
FRENCH.SOT:
Sabre utilisé par les Pirates et les pêcheurs.
Sa lame est parfaite pour nettoyer le poisson.
GERMAN.SOT:
A cutlass used by Pirates and fishermen alike.
Its edge is perfect for cleaning fish.
SPANISH.SOT:
Tanto piratas como pescadores usan este sable.
La hoja es ideal para limpiar pescado.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An old sword that once belonged to a Valuan
Admiral when he was stationed in Esparanza.
FRENCH.SOT:
Vieille épée qui appartenait jadis à un Amiral
Valuan lorsqu'il était posté à Esparanza.
GERMAN.SOT:
An old sword that once belonged to a Valuan
Admiral when he was stationed in Esparanza.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un viejo sable que antaño perteneció a un
almirante de Valua que estuvo en Esperanza.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A favorite among assassins of the world, mainly
because it has a chance to poison its target.
FRENCH.SOT:
Épée préférée des assassins du monde entier,
pour son pouvoir d'empoisonnement.
GERMAN.SOT:
A favorite among assassins of the world, mainly
because it has a chance to poison its target.
SPANISH.SOT:
Favorita de los asesinos de todo el mundo,
sobre todo porque envenena todo lo que corta.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An ancient cutlass made from Yeligar's hardened
skin. Some say it can cut through lightning.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un sabre ancien fabriqué en peau durcie de
Yeligar. On raconte qu'il peut fendre un éclair.
GERMAN.SOT:
An ancient cutlass made from Yeligar's hardened
skin. Some say it can cut through lightning.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un sable antiguo hecho con la curtida piel de
Yeligar. Dicen que corta los rayos.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An ancient blade of pre-Old World times, it is
said that this blade was used to cut iron ore.
FRENCH.SOT:
Ancienne épée datant d'avant l'Ancien Monde, on
dit qu'elle servait à couper le minerai de fer.
GERMAN.SOT:
An ancient blade of pre-Old World times, it is
said that this blade was used to cut iron ore.
SPANISH.SOT:
Una espada anterior al Mundo Antiguo
que antano se utilizaba para cortar el hierro.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A cutlass used by desert-faring merchants for
self-defense, its blade is finely worked stone.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un sabre utilisé par les marchands du désert
pour se défendre; lame taillée dans la pierre.
GERMAN.SOT:
A cutlass used by desert-faring merchants for
self-defense, its blade is finely worked stone.
SPANISH.SOT:
Los mercaderes del desierto lo usan para
defenderse. La hoja es de piedra tallada.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The sword of the great Air Pirate Daccat, it has
the power to lull enemies to sleep.
FRENCH.SOT:
L'épée du grand Pirate Daccat a le
pouvoir d'endormir les ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
The sword of the great Air Pirate Daccat, it has
the power to lull enemies to sleep.
SPANISH.SOT:
La espada del gran pirata aéreo Daccat sirve para
adormecer al enemigo completamente.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A hunting blade fashioned to resemble a beast's
fang. A favorite among Ixa'takan warriors.
FRENCH.SOT:
Lame de chasse conçue comme un croc d'animal.
Épée préférée des guerriers Ixa'takan.
GERMAN.SOT:
A hunting blade fashioned to resemble a beast's
fang. A favorite among Ixa'takan warriors.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un arma de caza que imita la dentadura de un
animal. Preferida por los guerreros Ixa'takan.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A blade originally used in masonry work, it has
since been modified to be used in combat.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une lame utilisée à l'origine en maçonnerie, qui
a été modifiée pour servir dans les combats.
GERMAN.SOT:
A blade originally used in masonry work, it has
since been modified to be used in combat.
SPANISH.SOT:
Una espada que se utilizaba en albañilería,
pero se ha transformado para su uso en combate.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A legendary sword that can supposedly rip the
fabric of reality and make dreams come true.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une épée légendaire qui peut soi-disant déchirer
le tissu de la réalité et réaliser les rêves.
GERMAN.SOT:
A legendary sword that can supposedly rip the
fabric of reality and make dreams come true.
SPANISH.SOT:
Mitica espada que deshace la materia de lo real
para que los suenos se hagan realidad.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A blade so slender that it is fabled to be able
to cut the very air in half.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une épée si fine qu'elle peut couper l'air
d'après la légende.
GERMAN.SOT:
A blade so slender that it is fabled to be able
to cut the very air in half.
SPANISH.SOT:
Espada de hoja tan fina que, según la leyenda,
corta el mismisimo aire por la mitad.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A masterpiece of the legendary swordsmith,
Ryu-kan, forged from Velorium.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un chef d'oeuvre du légendaire façonneur d'épée,
Ryu-kan, forgée en Velorium.
GERMAN.SOT:
A masterpiece of the legendary swordsmith,
Ryu-kan, forged from Velorium.
SPANISH.SOT:
Una obra maestra del mítico creador de espadas
Ryu-kan, forjada con Velorium.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A short sword used by Yafutoman soldiers, its
thick, heavy blade is still easy to handle.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une courte épée dont se servaient les soldats
Yafutoman, à lame large et lourde mais maniable.
GERMAN.SOT:
A short sword used by Yafutoman soldiers, its
thick, heavy blade is still easy to handle.
SPANISH.SOT:
Espada corta usada por los soldados Yafutoman.
Aunque sea gruesa y pesada, es fácil de manejar.

ENGLISH.SOT:
The ultimate sword, the best work of the master
swordsmith, Ryu-kan. Can cause instant death.
FRENCH.SOT:
L'ultime épée, le meilleur travail du façonneur
d'épée, Ryu-kan. Peut tuer d'un seul coup.
GERMAN.SOT:
The ultimate sword, the best work of the master
swordsmith, Ryu-kan. Can cause instant death.
SPANISH.SOT:
La espada por antonomasia, obra maestra del
maestro Ryu-kan, que causa la muerte instantánea.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Aika's favorite boomerang. It's large but light,
and relatively easy to aim.
FRENCH.SOT:
Boomerang préféré d'Aika. Il est grand mais
léger et facile à lancer.
GERMAN.SOT:
Aika's favorite boomerang. It's large but light,
and relatively easy to aim.
SPANISH.SOT:
El boomerang preferido de Aika. Grande pero
ligero, y fácil de dirigir.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A boomerang shaped like a flying bird. It
always returns, no matter how far it is thrown.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang en forme d'oiseau. Il revient
toujours, quelle que soit la distance.
GERMAN.SOT:
A boomerang shaped like a flying bird. It
always returns, no matter how far it is thrown.
SPANISH.SOT:
Boomerang con forma de pájaro volador. Siempre
regresa, da igual lo lejos que sea lanzado.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A weapon carried by crews of scouting parties,
it is meant to be fast and deadly.
FRENCH.SOT:
Arme transportée par les équipes d'éclaireurs,
elle est conçue pour être rapide et mortelle.
GERMAN.SOT:
A weapon carried by crews of scouting parties,
it is meant to be fast and deadly.
SPANISH.SOT:
El arma que usan las tripulaciones de partidas de
reconocimiento. Debe ser rápida y mortal.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A boomerang with an icy clear, sharp blade that
seemingly freezes the air it flies through.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang à la lame glacée et aiguisée qui
semble gèler l'air qu'il fend.
GERMAN.SOT:
A boomerang with an icy clear, sharp blade that
seemingly freezes the air it flies through.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un boomerang de hoja afilada y transparente como
el hielo, que congela el aire que atraviesa.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A leather-reinforced boomerang that is very
sturdy in build, and packs an extra punch.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang en cuir renforcé qui est très
solide et particulièrement puissant.
GERMAN.SOT:
A leather-reinforced boomerang that is very
sturdy in build, and packs an extra punch.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un boomerang reforzado con cuero de hechura recia
y con un gran impacto.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An ancient weapon found near Sailors' Island.
Thought to have been used for wood & stone work.
FRENCH.SOT:
Ancienne arme trouvée près de l'île aux Marins.
Aurait servie au travail du bois & de la pierre.
GERMAN.SOT:
An ancient weapon found near Sailors' Island.
Thought to have been used for wood & stone work.
SPANISH.SOT:
Arma antigua de la Isla del Pirata. Se usaba para
trabajar la madera y la piedra.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A traditional Ixa'takan hunting weapon, children
are taught to use them from a very young age.
FRENCH.SOT:
Arme traditionnelle de chasse Ixa'takan, on
apprend très tôt aux enfants à s'en sevir.
GERMAN.SOT:
A traditional Ixa'takan hunting weapon, children
are taught to use them from a very young age.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un arma de caza tradicional de los Ixa'takan, que
los niños aprenden a manejar desde pequeños.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A light boomerang used to practice for the
annual boomerang contest in the Valuan Coliseum.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang léger qui sert pour l'entraînement
au championnat annuel du Coliseum Valuan.
GERMAN.SOT:
A light boomerang used to practice for the
annual boomerang contest in the Valuan Coliseum.
SPANISH.SOT:
Boomerang ligero con el que practicar para el
concurso anual del Coliseo de Valua.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A tear-shaped blade crafted by a master
weaponsmith from a single piece of Moon Stone.
FRENCH.SOT:
Épée en forme de larme réalisée par un grand
maître avec un seul morceau de Pierre de Lune.
GERMAN.SOT:
A tear-shaped blade crafted by a master
weaponsmith from a single piece of Moon Stone.
SPANISH.SOT:
Una espada en forma de lágrima creada por un
maestro artesano con una pieza de Piedra Lunar.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A decorative throwing blade used by Nasrean
dancers. It is used as a hunting weapon as well.
FRENCH.SOT:
Une épée de lancer décorative utilisée par les
danceurs Nasrean. Sert aussi d'arme de chasse.
GERMAN.SOT:
A decorative throwing blade used by Nasrean
dancers. It is used as a hunting weapon as well.
SPANISH.SOT:
Las bailarinas de Nasr usan este cuchillo
ornamental que sirve también para cazar.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Crafted in memory of those lost in the Dark Rift
and in hopes that others will fare better.
FRENCH.SOT:
Réalisée en mémoire des disparus du Récif Noir
dans l'espoir que d'autres s'en sortiront.
GERMAN.SOT:
Crafted in memory of those lost in the Dark Rift
and in hopes that others will fare better.
SPANISH.SOT:
Hecha en memoria de los desaparecidos en la
Gruta Oscura, para dar esperanza a los nuevos.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Used by guards in an ancient imperial palace,
this blade has the power to weaken enemies.
FRENCH.SOT:
Épée utilisée par les gardes d'un ancien palais
impérial, a le pouvoir d'affaiblir les ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
Used by guards in an ancient imperial palace,
this blade has the power to weaken enemies.
SPANISH.SOT:
Usada por los guardias de un antiguo palacio
imperial. Su función es debilitar al enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A superb weapon created by the master, Ryu-kan.
A perfect balance of design and functionality.
FRENCH.SOT:
Arme superbe créée par maître Ryu-kan. Parfait
équilibre entre fonctionnel et esthétique.
GERMAN.SOT:
A superb weapon created by the master, Ryu-kan.
A perfect balance of design and functionality.
SPANISH.SOT:
Insuperable arma creada por el maestro Ryu-kan.
Perfecto equilibrio de diseño y funcionalidad.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A boomerang modified by the Valuan army with
reinforcement for close-quarters combat.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang modifié par l'armée Valuan avec
renforcement pour les combats rapprochés.
GERMAN.SOT:
A boomerang modified by the Valuan army with
reinforcement for close-quarters combat.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un boomerang reforzado por el ejército de Valua
para usar en combates cuerpo a cuerpo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A boomerang made from a bone of the Green Gigas.
Its power rivals the Fist of Grendel.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un boomerang fabriqué avec un os de Gigas Vert.
Son pouvoir rivalise avec le Poing de Grendel.
GERMAN.SOT:
A boomerang made from a bone of the Green Gigas.
Its power rivals the Fist of Grendel.
SPANISH.SOT:
Boomerang hecho con un hueso del Gigas Verde.
Su poder es comparable al Puño de Grendel.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A double-bladed boomerang with an unpredictable
flight path. It can induce Confuse in enemies.
FRENCH.SOT:
Boomerang à double tranchant. Sa trajectoire
est imprévisible ce qui peut tromper l'ennemi.
GERMAN.SOT:
A double-bladed boomerang with an unpredictable
flight path. It can induce Confuse in enemies.
SPANISH.SOT:
Boomerang de doble hoja cuya trayectoria de vuelo
es impredecible. Confunde al enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An artificial life form created by Silvites.
Cupil has been with Fina since she was 4.
FRENCH.SOT:
Espèce artificielle créée par les Silvites.
Cupil accompagne Fina depuis qu'elle a 4 ans.
GERMAN.SOT:
An artificial life form created by Silvites.
Cupil has been with Fina since she was 4.
SPANISH.SOT:
Forma de vida artificial creada por Silvites.
Fina recogió a Cupil cuando ella tenía 4 años.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a lance and lunges itself at
whatever enemy Fina commands.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en lance et se jette sur
l'ennemi au commandement de Fina.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a lance and lunges itself at
whatever enemy Fina commands.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil se transforma en lanza y se arroja contra
cualquier enemigo que Fina le ordene.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a star and spirals towards its
enemy.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en étoile et fonce en spirale
sur son ennemi.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a star and spirals towards its
enemy.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil se transforma en estrella y se lanza en
espiral contra el enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Morphs into a sharp cone, and lunges itself
at its enemies.
FRENCH.SOT:
Se change en cône pointu, et se jette sur ses
ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
Morphs into a sharp cone, and lunges itself
at its enemies.
SPANISH.SOT:
Se transforma en un cono afilado y arremete contra
el enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Morphs into a barbed spearhead. Each barb
helps Cupil inflict more damage.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en lance barbelée qui lui
permet de causer plus de dégâts.
GERMAN.SOT:
Morphs into a barbed spearhead. Each barb
helps Cupil inflict more damage.
SPANISH.SOT:
Se transforma en una punta de lanza con púas y
cada púa ayuda a Cupil a causar más daños.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil learns the ability to morph into an
extremely sharp knife.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil apprend à se changer en couteau
extrêmement tranchant.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil learns the ability to morph into an
extremely sharp knife.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil adquiere la habilidad de transformarse en un
cuchillo afiladísimo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
By morphing into a sword, Cupil can cleave
almost any enemy in two.
FRENCH.SOT:
En se changeant en épée, Cupil peut fendre en
deux presque tous les ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
By morphing into a sword, Cupil can cleave
almost any enemy in two.
SPANISH.SOT:
Transformándose en espada, Cupil puede partir
a casi todos sus enemigos por la mitad.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil learned to morph into a cutlass by
watching Vyse fight. Cupil Fury!!!
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil a appris à se changer en sabre en
regardant Vyse se battre. Furie de Cupil !!!
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil learned to morph into a cutlass by
watching Vyse fight. Cupil Fury!!!
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil aprende a transformarse en sable viendo
pelear a Vyse. Confunde al enemigo. ¡Furia Cupil!

ENGLISH.SOT:
Morphing into a giant 2-handed sword, Cupil can
cause massive amounts of damage on any enemy.
FRENCH.SOT:
En se changeant en épée géante à 2 lames,
Cupil peut gravement blesser l'ennemi.
GERMAN.SOT:
Morphing into a giant 2-handed sword, Cupil can
cause massive amounts of damage on any enemy.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil se convierte en una espada gigante de doble
hoja y causa muchos danos al enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Morphs into a small, but heavy, cannonball,
and drops on an enemy from high above.
FRENCH.SOT:
Se change en boule de canon, petite mais lourde
et tombe de haut sur un ennemi.
GERMAN.SOT:
Morphs into a small, but heavy, cannonball,
and drops on an enemy from high above.
SPANISH.SOT:
Se transforma en una pequeña, pero pesada, bala de
cañón y cae sobre el enemigo desde lo alto.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a spike-laden board and drops
on an enemy's head. It misses a lot, though.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en planche couverte de pointes
& tombe sur la tête d'un ennemi. Échoue souvent.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a spike-laden board and drops
on an enemy's head. It misses a lot, though.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil se convierte en una tabla llena de púas y
cae sobre sus enemigos. También falla mucho.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil uses magic to increase its own weight many
times over, and then drops on an enemy's head.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil fait un tour de magie pour augmenter son
poids, et tombe sur la tête d'un ennemi.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil uses magic to increase its own weight many
times over, and then drops on an enemy's head.
SPANISH.SOT:
Haciendo magia, Cupil multiplica su propio peso
y se deja caer sobre la cabeza del enemigo.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a frying pan and uses all of
its strength to whack enemies over their heads.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en poêle à frire et frappe de
toutes ses forces sur la tête des ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil morphs into a frying pan and uses all of
its strength to whack enemies over their heads.
SPANISH.SOT:
Cupil se transforma en sartén y golpea a sus
enemigos en la cabeza con todas sus fuerzas.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Morphs into a club and bludgeons enemies into
submission. Even Cupil has a mean-streak.
FRENCH.SOT:
Se change en massue et force les ennemis à se
soumettre. Même Cupil peut être méchant.
GERMAN.SOT:
Morphs into a club and bludgeons enemies into
submission. Even Cupil has a mean-streak.
SPANISH.SOT:
Se convierte en porra y golpea al enemigo hasta
que éste se rinde. Es el lado malvado de Cupil.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil morphs into the shape of a giant hammer
and hits enemies over their heads.
FRENCH.SOT:
Cupil se change en marteau géant et frappe
sur la tête des ennemis.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil morphs into the shape of a giant hammer
and hits enemies over their heads.
SPANISH.SOT:
Adopta la forma de un martillo gigante y
atiza a los enemigos en la cabeza.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Cupil's final and ultimate form, it looks very
impressive, and packs quite a punch.
FRENCH.SOT:
Forme finale et ultime de Cupil, très
impressionante et puissante.
GERMAN.SOT:
Cupil's final and ultimate form, it looks very
impressive, and packs quite a punch.
SPANISH.SOT:
La última y definitiva forma que Cupil adopta es
impresionante. Tiene gran impacto y potencia.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A mechanical arm that shows signs of rigorous
use over many years, yet it looks sturdy.
FRENCH.SOT:
Bras mécanique qui montre les signes d'un usage
intensif mais semble robuste.
GERMAN.SOT:
A mechanical arm that shows signs of rigorous
use over many years, yet it looks sturdy.
SPANISH.SOT:
Un brazo mecánico desgastado por muchos años de
uso, pero de aspecto resistente.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An attachment for Drachma's arm, it is a
hook-shaped blade that is razor sharp.
FRENCH.SOT:
Un accessoire pour le bras de Drachma, une épée
en forme de crochet, tranchante comme un rasoir.
GERMAN.SOT:
An attachment for Drachma's arm, it is a
hook-shaped blade that is razor sharp.
SPANISH.SOT:
Una extensión del brazo de Drachma. Una cuchilla
en forma de garfio y afilada como una navaja.

ENGLISH.SOT:
A heavy, spiked steel ball with awesome
destructive power, but low accuracy.
FRENCH.SOT:
Boule lourde, en acier avec des pointes, au
pouvoir destructeur immense mais guère précise.
GERMAN.SOT:
A heavy, spiked steel ball with awesome
destructive power, but low accuracy.
SPANISH.SOT:
Pesada bola de acero con púas con un increíble
poder destructivo, pero poca precisión.

ENGLISH.SOT:
Equipment designed to mine Moon Stones. Created
by De Loco when he was assigned to Ixa'taka.
FRENCH.SOT:
Équipement conçu pour extraire les Pierres de
Lune. Crée par De Loco à Ixa'taka.
GERMAN.SOT:
Equipment designed to mine Moon Stones. Created
by De Loco when he was assigned to Ixa'taka.
SPANISH.SOT:
Instrumento para extraer Piedras Lunares,
creado por De Loco al marcharse a Ixa'taka.

ENGLISH.SOT:
An arm specially designed for Drachma by the

FRENCH.SOT:

master swordsmith, Ryu-kan.

like a bird's beak. It can also Confuse enemies.

it can even be used for delicate movements.

left behind in the ruins of an ancient city.

Ryu-kan. It can also turn enemies to stone.

Can impose Silence on enemies.
SPANISH.SOT:

mysterious powers can put enemies to Sleep.

A gun that has gotten Gilder through many a
tight spot. Small, but easy to handle.

Este arma ha sacado a Gilder de muchos aprietos.

without the unnecessary decorative elements.

increase power, without sacrificing accuracy.

cause instant death with a good shot.

A gun made specifically to fit Gilder's touch.
It has unequaled accuracy and power.

Grande puissance d'attaque mais peu précise.

A special item for people on the Net.
Boasts high attack power, but low accuracy.

Un arma especial para pescadores con red.

A special item for people on the Net.

Réussira toujours à désorienter les ennemis.

A special item for people on the Net.

Uniform of the Blue Rogues.

Uniform of the Blue Rogues.
Given to him by his father.
SPANISH.SOT:

Aika's favorite pair of shorts, given to her

------

SPANISH.SOT:

zonas con bastante viento. No están mal.

decent meal. Can be eaten raw.

una buena comida. Pueden comerse crudos.

grotesque appearance, it tastes pretty good.

to catch smaller fish. These fish are delicious.

high altitudes, and has a bland taste.

Ocean. Very high in nutritional value.

the East raw, or cooked in broth.
SPANISH.SOT:

Une partie de ce mets délicat est comestible.

as a delicacy, but not much of it is edible.
SPANISH.SOT:

considera un manjar, pero tiene poca carne.

continents. Barely edible.

Sa viande est un mets délicat.

Very little is known about this rare creature.
Its meat is a delicacy.

Se sabe muy poco sobre esta extraña criatura.
Su carne es un manjar.

pay bags of gold just to look at it.
